The order of preference for distribution from the Fund shall be as follows:
disbursements from the Rate Stabilization Account to subsidize health care provider rates under § 19-805 of this subtitle;
disbursements from the Medical Assistance Program Account sufficient to:
pay for increased rates to health care providers identified under § 19-807(c)(2) of this subtitle; and
pay managed care organization health care providers identified under § 19-807(c)(2) of this subtitle consistent with the fee-for-service health care provider rate increases;
disbursements to maintain the increase in health care provider reimbursements under § 19-807(c)(2) of this subtitle;
disbursements to increase capitation payments to managed care organizations participating in the Maryland Medical Assistance Program consistent with § 15-103(b)(18) of the Health - General Article; and
disbursements from the Medical Assistance Program Account to:
increase fee-for-service health care provider rates under § 19-807 of this subtitle; and
pay managed care organization health care providers consistent with fee-for-service health care provider rates under § 19-807(c)(3) of this subtitle.
